    "title" : "Tests with shared (lengthy) setup",
    "body" : "<p>Suppose I have a test suit with a lengthy setup (perhaps, it's a GUI test).</p>\n<p>I don't want to execute the setup for each test method since I want the test suit to finish sooner.</p>\n<p>I also don't want to shove every possible assertion into one test method.</p>\n<p>Basically, I seem to want multiple &quot;independent&quot; test methods that share common setup (hence the quotes).</p>\n<p>Is it generally a good idea to have a shared setup for separate tests in such cases? Or does the risk of making the tests brittle outweigh any potential performance gains?</p>\n",
